    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> hot dog sausage[s]</strong> to one side of a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25 min or until the sausage is cooked through</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-mac-and-cheese-hot-dog/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sausages are cooking, slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> as thinly as you can</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> to a small bowl with your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>and set aside to pickle \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-mac-and-cheese-hot-dog/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>macaroni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 7 min or until it's cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>macaroni</strong>, reserving the pot</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-mac-and-cheese-hot-dog/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until golden, stirring frequently \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-mac-and-cheese-hot-dog/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux<strong> </strong>with your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and whisk for 3-4 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-mac-and-cheese-hot-dog/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>cooked macaroni </strong>and <strong>grated cheese</strong> to the pot with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up until fully coated and the cheese has melted \u2013 this is your <strong>macaroni cheese</strong></p><p>Once the sausages have had 25 min, add your <strong>hot dog bun[s] </strong>to the other side of the baking tray[s] and cook for 3 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-mac-and-cheese-hot-dog/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>, <strong>tomato wedges </strong>and <strong>quick-pickled shallot </strong>to a bowl with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tomato & shallot</strong> <strong>salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bbq-mac-and-cheese-hot-dog/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut a slit into the top of your<strong> hot dog bun[s]</strong></p><p>Fill each<strong> hot dog bun </strong>with a <strong>hot dog sausage</strong>, then top with some of the <strong>macaroni cheese</strong>, your <strong>BBQ sauce </strong>and some of the <strong>garlic breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> remaining macaroni cheese </strong>topped with the <strong>remaining garlic breadcrumbs </strong>and the <strong>tomato & shallot</strong> <strong>salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
